## 3. Existing Icon Usage in the Project

**There are NO icon libraries or icon components used anywhere in this project.**

Evidence:

- **`package.json`** (`/home/glompy/Desktop/ASTROCYTECH/Agent_X/ui/package.json`) lists only two runtime dependencies: `react` and `react-dom`. No icon libraries (Font Awesome, Material Icons, Heroicons, Lucide, Phosphor, etc.) are declared.

- **Grep for `icon|Icon|fa-|material|heroicon|lucide|fontawesome|svg|glyph`** across all `.tsx`, `.ts`, `.jsx`, `.js`, `.vue`, and `.css` files in the `ui/` directory returned **zero matches**.

- The only visual embellishments in the UI are:
  - Unicode characters used inline: `×` (close button, line 188), `■` (stop button, line 872), `▶` (send button, line 879), `—` (em dash fallback, lines 804/808/812), `…` (ellipsis in diff truncation, line 50 of ActivityPanel.jsx)
  - CSS class names like `btn-open`, `btn-rename`, `btn-delete`, `btn-clear` that only apply borders, colors, and backgrounds — no icon glyphs.

